1 Corporation or Securities Investor Protection Corporation
2 protections;
3 b. Legislative and regulatory changes or actions at the state,
4 federal, or international level may adversely affect the value of
5 virtual currency;
6 c. Transactions in virtual currency may be irreversible, and
7 accordingly, losses due to fraudulent or accidental transactions
8 may not be recoverable;
9 d. Some virtual currency transactions may be immediately effective
10 when recorded on a public ledger, which is not necessarily the
11 date or time that the user initiates the transaction;
12 e. The value of virtual currency may be derived from the continued
13 willingness of market participants to exchange legal tender for
14 virtual currency, which may result in the potential for permanent
15 and total loss of value of a particular virtual currency if the
16 market for the virtual currency declines or collapses for an
17 extended period of time;
18 f. Any surety bond required by Section 8 of this Act for the benefit
19 of users may not be sufficient to cover all losses incurred by the
20 users;
21 g. Users should perform research before purchasing or investing in
22 virtual currency; and
23 h. The circumstances under which the licensee will, in the ordinary
