14 1. The identification and assessment of fraud-related risk areas;
15 2. Procedures, controls, and monitoring mechanisms to protect against
16 identified risks;
17 3. Allocation of responsibility for monitoring risks; and
18 4. Procedures for the periodic evaluation and revision of the anti-fraud
19 procedures, controls, and monitoring mechanisms.
20 (4) (a) Each licensee shall implement, maintain, and enforce a written enhanced
21 due diligence policy.
22 (b) The enhanced due diligence policy shall:
23 1. Be reviewed and approved by the licensee's board of directors or
24 equivalent governing body; and
25 2. At a minimum, establish protocols to identify individuals who are at
