5 administrative regulation promulgated, or order issued or entered, under
6 this subtitle; or
7 (b) Secure information necessary for the proper enforcement of this subtitle.
8 (2) (a) The commissioner may conduct routine examinations of the virtual
9 currency kiosk affairs, business, offices, books, accounts, and records of
10 licensees.
11 (b) A licensee shall pay a reasonable fee sufficient to cover the cost of each
12 routine examination based upon fair compensation for time and actual
13 expenses.
14 (c) Upon written notice of the amount assessed under paragraph (b) of this
15 subsection, the licensee shall become liable for and pay the assessment to
16 the department.
17 (3) To the extent necessary to conduct any investigation or examination authorized
18 under this section, the commissioner may:
19 (a) Compel the attendance of any person or obtain any books, accounts, or
20 records by subpoenas;
21 (b) Administer oaths and affirmations; and
22 (c) Examine under oath or affirmation all persons whose testimony he or she
23 may require.
24 (4) As a condition of licensure under this subtitle, a licensee shall, by operation of
25 law, be deemed to consent to any examination or investigation conducted under
26 this section, whether or not prior notice is given to the licensee.
27 (5) When conducting an investigation or examination, the commissioner may do any
Page 38 of 51
XXXX 1/29/2026 12:32 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1829
1 of the following:
2 (a) Conduct an on-site or off-site investigation or examination;
3 (b) Participate in a joint or concurrent investigation or examination with one
4 (1) or more states or federal agencies, including a multistate investigation
5 or examination; and
6 (c) Accept and rely upon an investigation or examination report of one (1) or
7 more states or federal agencies, including a multistate investigation or
8 examination report.
9 (6) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection and Section 18 of
10 this Act, a routine examination report, related correspondence, and
11 examination-related information shall be considered confidential by law,
12 privileged, and not subject to disclosure under KRS 61.870 to 61.884.
13 (b) A licensee:
14 1. May disclose a Kentucky routine examination report to a financial
15 institution upon written request from the financial institution for the
16 purpose of assisting the financial institution in its compliance with the
17 Bank Secrecy Act, 31 U.S.C. secs. 5311 to 5332 and 31 C.F.R. pt. 103;
18 and
19 2. Shall provide written notice to the commissioner of a disclosure made
20 under this paragraph at the same time that the disclosure is made.
21 SECTION 18. A NEW SECTION OF SUBTITLE 13 OF KRS CHAPTER 286
22 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
23 (1) Except as otherwise provided in subsection (3) of this section, any document,
24 material, report, or other information in the possession or control of the
25 commissioner that is provided to the commissioner according to this subtitle
26 shall:
27 (a) Be confidential by law and privileged;
Page 39 of 51
