4 SECTION 20. A NEW SECTION OF SUBTITLE 13 OF KRS CHAPTER 286
5 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) As used in this section, "person" includes any applicant or licensee.
7 (2) (a) The commissioner shall serve written notice on an applicant prior to:
8 1. Conditionally issuing a license; or
9 2. Denying an application for any of the following:
10 a. A license;
11 b. A change of control; or
12 c. The replacement or addition of a responsible individual.
13 (b) An applicant that is served a notice under paragraph (a) of this subsection
14 shall be entitled to an administrative hearing on the notice conducted in
15 accordance with KRS Chapter 13B if the applicant files a written request
16 for a hearing with the commissioner within twenty (20) days of the date of
17 service.
18 (3) (a) The commissioner shall serve an administrative complaint on a person:
19 1. Prior to doing any of the following:
20 a. Suspending or revoking a person's license under Section 21 of
21 this Act;
22 b. Entering a cease and desist order against the person under
23 Section 23 of this Act; or
24 c. Entering an order against the person to pay any fee or penalty,
25 or provide any remedy, authorized under this subtitle; and
26 2. Simultaneous with the service of an emergency order on the person
27 under Section 22 of this Act.
