1 (b) Except as provided in paragraph (c) of this subsection, a person that is
2 served an administrative complaint under paragraph (a) of this subsection
3 shall be entitled to an administrative hearing on the complaint conducted in
4 accordance with KRS Chapter 13B if the person files both of the following
5 with the commissioner within twenty (20) days of the date of service:
6 1. A written answer to the complaint; and
7 2. A request for hearing.
8 (c) A person that complies with paragraph (b) of this subsection in response to
9 an administrative complaint and emergency order entered under Section 22
10 of this Act shall be entitled to an emergency administrative hearing
11 conducted in accordance with KRS 13B.125.
12 (4) (a) Except as provided in paragraph (b) of this subsection, the commissioner
13 shall serve any notice, complaint, or emergency order referenced in this
14 section by certified mail or personal delivery to the person's last known
15 address of record or upon the person's agent for service of process.
16 (b) If the commissioner is unable to reasonably determine a person's last
17 known address of record or agent for service of process, the commissioner
18 may serve a notice, a complaint, or an emergency order by certified mail or
19 personal delivery to any owner or operator of the premises or real property
20 upon which the person's virtual currency kiosk or kiosks are located.
21 (5) Service by certified mail shall be complete as provided in KRS 13B.050(2).
22 (6) If any person fails to timely file a request for hearing under subsection (2) of this
23 section, or a written answer and request for hearing under subsection (3) of this
24 section, the commissioner may, as applicable and subject to KRS Chapter 13B,
25 enter a final order:
26 (a) Taking the action that was:
27 1. Set forth in the notice; or
