1 2. Sought in the complaint; or
2 (b) Affirming the emergency action that was taken.
3 (7) All other requirements of and rights arising under KRS Chapter 13B shall apply
4 to administrative hearings conducted and orders issued under this subtitle.
5 (8) The commissioner may, at any time, enter into a consent order with any person to
6 resolve a matter arising under this subtitle.
7 SECTION 21. A NEW SECTION OF SUBTITLE 13 OF KRS CHAPTER 286
8 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
9 (1) As used in this section, "unsafe or unsound act or practice" means any of the
10 following:
11 (a) An act or practice that creates a likelihood of material loss, insolvency, or
12 dissipation of assets that materially prejudices the:
13 1. Financial condition of an applicant or a licensee; or
14 2. Interests of an applicant's or a licensee's customers; or
15 (b) Any other act or practice determined by the commissioner to be unsafe or
16 unsound in accordance with the requirements of this subtitle or other
17 applicable law.
18 (2) Subject to Section 20 of this Act and KRS 335B.020, the commissioner may deny,
19 suspend, or revoke a license if the commissioner finds one (1) or more of the
20 following:
21 (a) The applicant or licensee has:
22 1. Violated any provision of this subtitle;
23 2. Violated any consent order or compliance agreement entered into with
24 the commissioner;
25 3. Engaged in:
26 a. An unsafe or unsound act or practice;
27 b. An unfair, deceptive, or dishonest act or practice;
Page 45 of 51
XXXX 1/29/2026 12:32 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1829
1 c. Fraud or intentional misrepresentation; or
2 d. A misappropriation of legal tender, virtual currency, or other
3 value held by a fiduciary;
4 4. Misrepresented material facts or made a false promise likely to
5 influence, persuade, or induce a resident to engage in a virtual
6 currency kiosk transaction;
7 5. Misrepresented or concealed a material fact, term, or condition of a
8 virtual currency kiosk transaction;
9 6. Knowingly engaged in a transaction, practice, or course of business
10 that perpetrates a fraud upon any person in connection with a virtual
11 currency kiosk transaction;
12 7. Failed to exchange, transfer, or store, without just cause, any funds in
13 accordance with any agreement connected with a virtual currency
14 kiosk business;
15 8. Failed to account for or deliver to any person any legal tender, virtual
16 currency, precious metals, electronic certificates, or other assets
17 obtained in connection with a virtual currency kiosk business;
18 9. Refused to permit, or failed to cooperate substantially with, an
19 investigation or examination under this subtitle;
20 10. Failed, within a reasonable time, to furnish any information or file
21 any report required, or otherwise requested by the commissioner,
22 under this subtitle;
23 11. Knowingly employed or contracted with a responsible individual that
24 has been convicted of, pled guilty to, or pled nolo contendere to a
25 felony; or
26 12. Has had any license, registration, claim of exemption, or other
27 authorization to do business relating to the financial services industry
