8 similar capacity in a case or other proceeding under any
9 bankruptcy, reorganization, arrangement, readjustment,
10 insolvency, receivership, dissolution, liquidation, or similar law;
11 and
12 b. Not obtained from a court, within a reasonable time,
13 confirmation of a plan or dismissal of the case or proceeding; or
14 4. Has applied for, or has permitted the appointment of, a receiver,
15 trustee, or other agent of a court for itself or for a substantial part of
16 its assets;
17 (c) The applicant or licensee has knowingly made or provided, or caused to be
18 made or provided, to the commissioner one (1) or more of the following:
19 1. A material misrepresentation; or
20 2. A false or fraudulent:
21 a. Material fact; or
22 b. Financial statement;
23 (d) The applicant or licensee suppressed or withheld from the commissioner
24 any information which, if submitted by the applicant or licensee, warrants
