UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1829
1 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
2 (1) As used in this section, "emergency order" means an order that does one (1) or
3 more the following without prior notice and hearing:
4 (a) Suspends any license; or
5 (b) Directs any peace officer to:
6 1. Seize or impound a virtual currency kiosk, including any contents
7 thereof; or
8 2. Render a virtual currency kiosk inoperable.
9 (2) Subject to Section 20 of this Act, the commissioner may enter an emergency order
10 against any licensee or other person, pending further investigation, the entry of a
11 final order, or other final legal action, if the commissioner has reason to believe,
12 or determines, one (1) or more of the following:
13 (a) The person is acting in violation of Section 3 of this Act;
14 (b) The licensee is not in compliance with Section 8 of this Act;
15 (c) The licensee or person has committed a material violation of this subtitle
16 that poses an immediate and irreparable harm to the public health, safety,
17 or welfare;
18 (d) The licensee has submitted a payment of any fee or penalty authorized
19 under this subtitle that was returned, declined, denied, dishonored, or
20 otherwise not paid in full for any reason;
21 (e) Subject to KRS 335B.020, the licensee is knowingly employing or
22 contracting with a responsible individual that has been convicted of, pled
23 guilty to, or pled nolo contendere to a felony; or
24 (f) The licensee has had any license, registration, claim of exemption, or other
25 authorization to do business relating to the financial services industry
26 denied, revoked, suspended, or terminated by any state or federal
27 jurisdiction.
