6 commissioner; or
7 2. Terminated by court order.
8 SECTION 23. A NEW SECTION OF SUBTITLE 13 OF KRS CHAPTER 286
9 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
10 (1) Subject to Section 20 of this Act, the commissioner may enter a cease and desist
11 order requiring an applicant, a licensee, or any other person to cease and desist
12 from violating one (1) or more identified provisions of the following, if the
13 commissioner has reason to believe or determines that the violations have
14 occurred or will occur:
15 (a) This subtitle;
16 (b) An administrative regulation promulgated under this subtitle;
17 (c) An order issued or entered under this subtitle; or
18 (d) An agreement entered with the commissioner relating to compliance with
19 this subtitle.
20 (2) A cease and desist order entered under this section shall remain in effect until it
21 is:
22 (a) Stayed, withdrawn, suspended, or superseded by order of the commissioner;
23 or
24 (b) Terminated by court order.
25 SECTION 24. A NEW SECTION OF SUBTITLE 13 OF KRS CHAPTER 286
26 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
27 (1) As used in this section, "person" includes any applicant or licensee.
