1 (2) Subject to Section 20 of this Act, the commissioner may do one (1) or more of the
2 following:
3 (a) Enter an order against any person to:
4 1. Refund any amount charged or collected in violation of this subtitle;
5 or
6 2. Pay any fee, or provide any other remedy, authorized under this
7 subtitle; and
8 (b) Levy a civil penalty against any person that violates, or participates in the
9 violation of, any:
10 1. Provision of this subtitle;
11 2. Administrative regulation promulgated under this subtitle;
12 3. Order issued or entered under this subtitle; or
13 4. Agreement with the commissioner relating to compliance with this
14 subtitle.
15 (3) The civil penalty levied under subsection (2)(b) of this section:
16 (a) Shall be not less than one thousand dollars ($1,000) nor more than five
17 thousand dollars ($5,000) per violation; and
18 (b) May:
19 1. Be assessed for each day the violation is outstanding; and
20 2. Include an order for the person to pay the state's costs and expenses
21 for the examination, investigation, and prosecution of the matter,
22 including reasonable attorney's fees and court costs.
23 Section 25. Sections 1 to 24 of this Act take effect March 31, 2027.
24 Section 26. On or before January 1, 2027, the commissioner of the Kentucky
25 Department of Financial Institutions shall promulgate any emergency and ordinary
26 administrative regulations required under Sections 1 to 24 of this Act.
